I absolutely agree, but there are already a number of posts out there that attempt to compare them despite solving different problems (binding framework vs SPA framework). Many compare the two directly, pointing out all of the functionality AngilarJS has that knockout doesn&#039;t. Some then mention you can use Durandel or add extra scripts to fill the gaps. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I thought the comparison could be done better, by showing how to provide those capabilities to a knockout example that makes it comparable to AngularJS. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I expected this to turn into an AngularJS vs Durandel post, because so many posts had made it sound complicated or complex to add scripts to have similar behavior with knockout, but I managed to get through the whole set of examples without once pulling in Durandel and only just realized that it is still in the list above and I have no working examples using it. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
So, yeah, knockout vs AngularJS isn&#039;t a one-to-one comparison, but I think knockout + packages vs AngularJS certainly is and it certainly helped me understand that the boogie man of &quot;you have to add more packages&quot; is not as bad as people want us to believe.&lt;br /&gt;
